trans: 脱下，褪下（紧身的衣服，尤指把里面外翻）

tr: the rind of a fruit or vegetable

example: please don't undress in front of everybody!
She strips in front of strangers every night for a living

tr: come off in flakes or thin small pieces
example: The paint in my house is peeling off

value.def: The peel of a fruit such as a lemon or an apple is its skin.

posc.def: You can also refer to a peel.

value.def: When you peel fruit or vegetables, you remove their skins.

example.ex: She sat down in the kitchen and began peeling potatoes.
example.tran: 她坐在厨房里，开始削土豆皮。

value.def: If you peel off something that has been sticking to a surface or if it peels off, it comes away from the surface.

example.ex: One of the kids was peeling plaster off the wall...
example.tran: 其中一个孩子在剥墙上的灰泥。

example.ex: It took me two days to peel off the labels...
example.tran: 我花了两天时间才揭下这些标签。

example.ex: Paint was peeling off the walls...
The wallpaper was peeling away close to the ceiling.
example.tran: 天花板附近的壁纸在剥落。

example.ex: ...an unrenovated bungalow with slightly peeling blue paint.
example.tran: 蓝漆略微剥落的失修平房

value.def: If a surface is peeling, the paint on it is coming away.

example.ex: Its once-elegant white pillars are peeling.
example.tran: 曾经典雅的白色立柱正在掉漆。

value.def: If you are peeling or if your skin is peeling, small pieces of skin are coming off, usually because you have been burned by the sun.

example.ex: His face, at the moment, was peeling from sunburn.
example.tran: 那时他的脸因为晒伤而脱皮。

trans: 桔皮状（硅片不正常状态）；（轨制金属的）粒状（疙瘩状）表面；桔皮面（形）（铸件缺陷）；明气孔；表面针孔
